# ✅ .github/workflows/github-secrets-setup.md
# GitHub Secrets Setup Guide

## Required Secrets

### Backend Deployment (Railway)
1. Go to GitHub repo → Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions
2. Add the following secrets:

- `DATABASE_URL`: Get from Railway PostgreSQL service
  Example: postgresql://user:password@containers-us-west-1.railway.app:7432/railway
  
- `JWT_SECRET`: Generate with:
```bash
  node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(64).toString('hex'))"
```

### Frontend Deployment (Vercel)
- `VERCEL_TOKEN`: Get from https://vercel.com/account/tokens
- `VERCEL_ORG_ID`: Run `vercel` CLI and check .vercel/project.json
- `VERCEL_PROJECT_ID`: Same as above
- `VITE_API_BASE_URL`: Your Railway backend URL (e.g., https://your-app.up.railway.app/api)

### Optional
- `CODECOV_TOKEN`: From https://codecov.io (for code coverage)